 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-alb","title":"P3.3 Extend SearchHit with provenance fields","description":"# P3.3 Extend SearchHit with provenance fields

## Overview
Add provenance metadata to the SearchHit struct so search results carry
source information for display and further processing.

## Implementation Details

### SearchHit Extension
In `src/lib.rs`, extend the SearchHit struct:
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct SearchHit {
    // ... existing fields
    pub conversation_id: String,
    pub agent: String,
    pub workspace: String,
    pub snippet: String,
    pub score: f32,
    pub timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,

    // New provenance fields
    pub source_hostname: Option<String>,
    pub source_type: SourceType,
    pub sync_timestamp: Option<DateTime<Utc>>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, Default)]
pub enum SourceType {
    #[default]
    Local,
    Remote,
}
```

### Tantivy Result Population
When building SearchHit from Tantivy document:
```rust
fn doc_to_search_hit(doc: &Document, schema: &Schema) -> SearchHit {
    let source_hostname = doc.get_first(schema.get_field("source_hostname")?)
        .and_then(|v| v.as_text())
        .map(String::from);

    let source_type = doc.get_first(schema.get_field("source_type")?)
        .and_then(|v| v.as_text())
        .map(|s| match s {
            "remote" => SourceType::Remote,
            _ => SourceType::Local,
        })
        .unwrap_or_default();

    // ... build SearchHit with these fields
}
```

## Dependencies
- Requires P1.4 (Tantivy schema has provenance fields)
- Blocks P3.4 (robot output needs these fields)

