 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-an73","title":"P6.3: Performance Benchmarks","description":"# P6.3: Performance Benchmarks

## Goal
Establish performance baselines for all critical operations and prevent regressions across desktop and mobile. Provide clear, measurable targets and automated checks.

## Performance Targets

| Metric | Target | Archive Size / Notes |
|--------|--------|----------------------|
| Initial page load (auth UI ready) | < 3s on 3G | All |
| Argon2id derivation | < 5s | All (threads vary by browser) |
| DB load (OPFS) | < 2s | < 50 MB |
| DB load (OPFS) | < 10s | < 200 MB |
| Search latency | < 100 ms | 10K+ rows |
| Virtual scroll | 60 fps | 100K+ results |
| Decrypt + decompress | < 1s | 10 MB payload |
| Memory usage | No unbounded growth | Long sessions |

## Benchmark Suites

### Rust (Criterion)
- crypto_perf.rs: Argon2id, AES-256-GCM, chunked encryption
- db_perf.rs: SQLite open, FTS queries, result pagination
- export_perf.rs: export + compression + chunking

### Browser Benchmarks
- Page load timing: navigation -> auth UI ready
- Decrypt timing: password -> DB ready
- Search latency: query -> render time
- Virtual scroll FPS during rapid scroll
- Memory usage tracking (WASM heap + JS heap)

## Test Matrix

| Browser | Device | Network | Archive Size |
|---------|--------|---------|--------------|
| Chrome | Desktop | Fast | Small / Medium / Large |
| Firefox | Desktop | Fast | Medium / Large |
| Safari | Mac | Fast | Medium |
| Chrome Mobile | Pixel | 4G | Small |
| Safari Mobile | iPhone | 4G | Small |

## Automation
- `scripts/bench_pages.sh` runs Rust benches and browser tests
- `scripts/check_bench_regression.py` fails if regression > 10%
- JSON + text logs with timestamps and per-phase durations

## Test Requirements
- Benchmarks are deterministic and stable enough for CI
- Clear log output for each phase
- Performance baselines documented in docs/PERFORMANCE.md

## Files to Create/Modify
- benches/crypto_perf.rs
- benches/db_perf.rs
- benches/export_perf.rs
- web/tests/performance.test.js
- scripts/bench_pages.sh
- scripts/check_bench_regression.py
- docs/PERFORMANCE.md

## Exit Criteria
