## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Generates SourceDefinition from probe results
- [ ] Includes only detected agent paths (unless user adds more)
- [ ] Generates sensible path mappings
- [ ] Shows preview before writing
- [ ] Allows customization of paths/mappings before save
- [ ] Allows adding custom paths not auto-detected
- [ ] Creates backup of existing config before modifying
- [ ] Validates TOML round-trip before writing
- [ ] Writes atomically (temp file + rename)
- [ ] Merges with existing config without data loss
- [ ] Skips already-configured sources
- [ ] Shows what was added/skipped
- [ ] Works in non-interactive mode (skip preview, use defaults)

## Dependencies
- Requires: SSH probing (coding_agent_session_search-vxe2) - for detected_agents
- Requires: Host selection (coding_agent_session_search-rnjt) - for selected hosts

## Considerations
- Backup retention: Keep last N backups? Or just one?
- Should we offer to update existing sources? (Currently: skip)
- Path mapping conflicts handled by showing both and letting user pick
- Custom paths: validate they look like paths (start with ~ or /)

